sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1675006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Construct the JBA (J23119+B0034+NhaA), B0034 and NhaB with the vector pSB1C3. Two functional genes NhaA and NhaB are used to pump in protons and lower the pH of bacteria???s microenvironment. JBA and JBB are linked with pSB1C3 through 3A Assemble successfully. Thus, it can be an alkaline-resisting part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: JIAQI XU
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence of promoter J23119 is found through the standard part BBa_J23119 http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_J23119 The sequence of ribosome binding site B0034 is found through the standard part BBa_B0034 http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_B0034 The sequence of gene NhaA is found through Genbank http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/NC_000913.3?report=genbank&from=17489&to=18655 The sequence of gene NhaB is found through Genbank http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/NC_000913.3?report=genbank&from=1233176&to=1234717&strand=true
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This is a composite part including the J23119 promoter ecoded in part BBa_J23119 and the ribosome binding site B0034 ecoded in part BBa_B0034. The functional genes NhaA and NhaB are cloned from Escherichia coli str. K-12 substr. sequence found through Genbank http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/NC_000913.3?report=genbank&from=17489&to=18655 http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/NC_000913.3?report=genbank&from=1233176&to=1234717&strand=true

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1675001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The gene, NhaB, is the archetypal sodium-proton antiporter in E. coli. It is crucial when the level of NhaA activity is growth limiting, when NhaA is not sufficiently induced, or when NhaA is not activated. NhaA catalyzes the exchange of 3 proton ion per 2 sodium ion. Therefore, NhaA could make sure E. coli???s survival under alkaline pH, which are in desperate need in our project.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: JIAQI XU
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Escherichia coli str. K-12 substr. Sequence found through Genbank http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/NC_000913.3?report=fasta&from=1233176&to=1234717&strand=true
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: mutation of CTG to CTA Leu.(site:336bp); mutation of GCT to GCG Ala.(site:414bp); mutation of ACC to ACT Thr.(site:519bp); mutation of GAC to GAT Asp.(site:525bp); mutation of ACC to ACT Thr.(site:630bp); mutation of GTA to GTG Val.(site:645bp); mutation of GCA to GCG Ala.(site:993bp); mutation of GAG to GAA Glu.(site:1020bp); mutation of GTC to GTA Val.(site:1452bp)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1675000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The gene,NhaA, is the archetypal sodium-proton antiporter in E. coli. It is the only member of the family that is absolutely required by E. coli for survival in high-salt conditions, under alkaline stress, or in the presence of otherwise toxic Li+ concentration. NhaA catalyzes the exchange of 2 H+ per Na+. Therefore, nhaA could make sure E. coli???s survival under alkaline pH, which are in desperate need in our project.
